00:11:17.560 --> 00:11:19.800
with Task is virtually
nonexistent.

00:11:19.800 --> 00:11:22.470
They've used a standard action
bar with icons and make it

00:11:22.470 --> 00:11:25.840
immediately obvious how to add
new items to your list.

00:11:25.840 --> 00:11:28.190
The view page is a simple
and obvious way to

00:11:28.190 --> 00:11:29.330
switch between lists.

00:11:29.330 --> 00:11:30.250
We love it.

00:11:30.250 --> 00:11:32.650
And we also love small touches
that help make this app

00:11:32.650 --> 00:11:35.340
particularly intuitive, like the
ability to drag and drop

00:11:35.340 --> 00:11:38.550
items in the list
to reorder them.

00:11:38.550 --> 00:11:41.460
They've also included some
excellent interactive widgets

00:11:41.460 --> 00:11:42.910
which use the same
design language.

00:11:42.910 --> 00:11:45.960
And we love us some widgets.

00:11:45.960 --> 00:11:49.300
The tablet layout is exactly
what you'd expect.

00:11:49.300 --> 00:11:52.890
Similarly intuitive, standard
multi-pane approach with a

00:11:52.890 --> 00:11:55.120
fragment on the left and a
fragment on the right which

00:11:55.120 --> 00:11:57.750
basically just removes a level
of navigation by letting you

00:11:57.750 --> 00:12:01.060
modify your tasks while the
list is still visible.

00:12:01.060 --> 00:12:04.040
Notice also, on this version,
they've implemented a

00:12:04.040 --> 00:12:08.480
contextual action bar which
is very tablet-y.

00:12:08.480 --> 00:12:11.410
So really well done there.

00:12:11.410 --> 00:12:14.260
Now we also spoke to Jorim from
Task Team to find out a

00:12:14.260 --> 00:12:17.140
little more about how he created
this Pure Android

00:12:17.140 --> 00:12:17.490
experience.

00:12:17.490 --> 00:12:21.100
RETO MEIER: Let's
listen to him.

00:12:21.100 --> 00:12:22.840
JORIM JAGGI: Hi, my
name is Jorim.

00:12:22.840 --> 00:12:25.440
I'm one of the developers
of the app

00:12:25.440 --> 00:12:28.280
Tasks, from Team Tasks.

00:12:28.280 --> 00:12:31.860
The app is basically designed
to sync with Google Tasks.

00:12:31.860 --> 00:12:34.880
It's a relatively simple app,
where you can add your

00:12:34.880 --> 00:12:39.410
personal tasks and show them in
Gmail and check them off.

00:12:43.200 --> 00:12:45.890
The app is now like nine
months on Google Play.

00:12:45.890 --> 00:12:48.470
It was released in April.

00:12:48.470 --> 00:12:51.510
We had huge success with
engagement and ratings and,

00:12:51.510 --> 00:12:53.730
yeah, it's a pretty cool app.

00:12:53.730 --> 00:12:59.190
Based on the feedback of Google
Developer Advocates, we

00:12:59.190 --> 00:13:01.970
implemented that you can set
customer reminder times for

00:13:01.970 --> 00:13:04.580
every task.

00:13:04.580 --> 00:13:06.520
But this is not synced
with Google Tasks

00:13:06.520 --> 00:13:09.870
because it's not possible.

00:13:09.870 --> 00:13:15.800
And also we did some minor clean
up, like, the Up button

00:13:15.800 --> 00:13:18.770
on the Home screen was
pressable, but it didn't have

00:13:18.770 --> 00:13:19.330
any action.

00:13:19.330 --> 00:13:22.560
So we cleaned some stuff
like that up.

00:13:22.560 --> 00:13:25.790
Like the change we did for the
reminder times helped ratings

00:13:25.790 --> 00:13:27.020
and comments a lot.

00:13:27.020 --> 00:13:29.900
It was like the number one
complaint about the app, that

00:13:29.900 --> 00:13:32.770
people can't set custom reminder
times, and I can

00:13:32.770 --> 00:13:33.900
understand why.

00:13:33.900 --> 00:13:35.970
Although, it's kind of hard
for us because we really

00:13:35.970 --> 00:13:40.100
designed the app to be
like the Google Tasks

00:13:40.100 --> 00:13:41.460
client you can use.

00:13:41.460 --> 00:13:44.470
And as soon as we implement
functionality, which we can't

00:13:44.470 --> 00:13:45.900
sync, we have kind
of a problem.

00:13:45.900 --> 00:13:50.170
So this is kind of a trade off
between a useful feature and

00:13:50.170 --> 00:13:53.130
not being able to sync that.

00:13:53.130 --> 00:13:57.020
But it helped a lot for our
ratings and comments.

00:13:57.020 --> 00:14:01.675
So the most challenging parts
really the sync part.

00:14:04.330 --> 00:14:09.240
It sounds pretty simple to sync
all your tasks with the

00:14:09.240 --> 00:14:10.600
Google back end.

00:14:10.600 --> 00:14:13.320
Sounds really simple, but it
gets really complicated

00:14:13.320 --> 00:14:15.250
because it can have nests
of self tasks.

00:14:15.250 --> 00:14:19.150
And then, what happens if you
delete the parent what happens

00:14:19.150 --> 00:14:21.330
if the child, and
all this stuff.

00:14:21.330 --> 00:14:25.040
And what we did there is kind
of we unit tested the whole

00:14:25.040 --> 00:14:28.740
thing so that we were
sure that the

00:14:28.740 --> 00:14:30.620
sync is working properly.

00:14:30.620 --> 00:14:33.640
Because the sync code is kind
of the heart of the

00:14:33.640 --> 00:14:34.750
application.

00:14:34.750 --> 00:14:36.850
It's kind of the most important
stuff that the sync

00:14:36.850 --> 00:14:38.750
always works.

00:14:38.750 --> 00:14:41.780
And, yeah, that was kind of
really challenging, but it

00:14:41.780 --> 00:14:42.310
worked out.

00:14:42.310 --> 00:14:44.530
And we had almost no bugs.

00:14:44.530 --> 00:14:48.290
We had some, a few bugs there,
but we figured it out.

00:14:48.290 --> 00:14:51.630
Our app adapts itself to
the different device

00:14:51.630 --> 00:14:52.290
configurations.

00:14:52.290 --> 00:14:56.360
We basically design the app to
be compatible with four--

00:14:56.360 --> 00:14:59.420
no, the three main buckets.

00:14:59.420 --> 00:15:02.190
The size of a Nexus 4, the size
of a Nexus 7, and the

00:15:02.190 --> 00:15:04.280
size of Nexus 10.

00:15:04.280 --> 00:15:07.350
On a Nexus 4, you just
see the task list.

00:15:07.350 --> 00:15:10.610
And then if you press your
task, you can edit it.

00:15:10.610 --> 00:15:13.450
And on a Nexus 7, it's
kind of the same.

00:15:13.450 --> 00:15:17.360
But if you rotated into
landscape, you see your tasks

00:15:17.360 --> 00:15:20.770
on the left and the task
detail on the right.

00:15:20.770 --> 00:15:24.600
So you can edit the task while
doing other tasks.

00:15:24.600 --> 00:15:29.120
And on the Nexus 10 it's still
the same, but with more

00:15:29.120 --> 00:15:32.770
spacing and bigger font sizes
and all this stuff.

00:15:32.770 --> 00:15:37.050
But really designed to work
from the ground up.

00:15:37.050 --> 00:15:40.030
We were clear this app has to
work with all kind of devices.

00:15:40.030 --> 00:15:42.700
And Android makes it really
easy, I have to say.

00:15:42.700 --> 00:15:45.550
They have a really powerful
resource system.

00:15:45.550 --> 00:15:51.230
Select the correct resources
helped design apps that better

00:15:51.230 --> 00:15:53.930
work with all screen sizes.

00:15:53.930 --> 00:15:56.790
So our design process like

00:15:56.790 --> 00:15:58.440
[INAUDIBLE], we do some sketches.

00:15:58.440 --> 00:16:01.570
But then start implementing them
right away, because we

00:16:01.570 --> 00:16:04.450
are more developers.

00:16:04.450 --> 00:16:11.620
And it's really easy with the
tool in Eclipse now to do the

00:16:11.620 --> 00:16:14.960
[INAUDIBLE] like writing code
and reuse it when you are

00:16:14.960 --> 00:16:17.330
really want to implement
it to the whole design.

00:16:17.330 --> 00:16:21.740
And we go normally from sketches
to implementation

00:16:21.740 --> 00:16:22.880
right away.

00:16:22.880 --> 00:16:26.180
And then iterate, of course,
with designers.

00:16:26.180 --> 00:16:29.480
So my favorite part about
developing on the Android is

00:16:29.480 --> 00:16:37.610
that you can design one app
and it runs on like 1,000

00:16:37.610 --> 00:16:38.660
different devices.

00:16:38.660 --> 00:16:39.820
That's really great.

00:16:39.820 --> 00:16:44.100
And also Android provides a lot
of useful tools to achieve

00:16:44.100 --> 00:16:46.610
that, to have a response
to design on

00:16:46.610 --> 00:16:48.780
every of these devices.

00:16:48.780 --> 00:16:54.340
So for example, the density
independent stuff.

00:16:54.340 --> 00:17:01.500
It just runs everywhere and
also the whole thing with

00:17:01.500 --> 00:17:05.680
fragments and the resource
system that you can have

00:17:05.680 --> 00:17:09.260
fragments for this device, but
not on this screen size.

00:17:09.260 --> 00:17:16.640
And that's really, really
pleasing that now I developed,

00:17:16.640 --> 00:17:21.190
basically, for testing we used
these three devices.

00:17:21.190 --> 00:17:25.670
A four inch phone, seven inch
tablet and a ten inch tablet,

00:17:25.670 --> 00:17:30.230
then also a legacy device with
Android 2.2 for backwards

00:17:30.230 --> 00:17:31.370
compatibility.

00:17:31.370 --> 00:17:35.202
But then after that we didn't
have a single issue that it

00:17:35.202 --> 00:17:36.090
didn't run on a device.

00:17:36.090 --> 00:17:37.630
That was really great.

00:17:37.630 --> 00:17:40.990
That you have like four devices
to test and it runs

00:17:40.990 --> 00:17:42.620
everywhere.

00:17:42.620 --> 00:17:47.190
So our next steps for the app
is kind of to integrate the

00:17:47.190 --> 00:17:49.150
emails into the tasks.

00:17:49.150 --> 00:17:54.590
There is a feature in Gmail
where you can add an email to

00:17:54.590 --> 00:17:56.020
your task list.

00:17:56.020 --> 00:17:59.220
And we just don't show
it on the device.

00:17:59.220 --> 00:18:03.270
So we really would like to sync
all these email stuff

00:18:03.270 --> 00:18:07.560
into the device and as soon as
you click on the link, you can

00:18:07.560 --> 00:18:11.650
see the email in the mobile
web browser and stuff.

00:18:11.650 --> 00:18:15.720
Besides that, we are also
looking with integrating our

00:18:15.720 --> 00:18:25.080
data with third party widgets
like simple widgets, whatever.

00:18:25.080 --> 00:18:28.220
There are lots of them and
they're all asking for a

00:18:28.220 --> 00:18:31.800
content provider that
we provide.

00:18:31.800 --> 00:18:36.100
So the users can show their
tasks on the custom.

00:18:36.100 --> 00:18:38.730
They're really customized
widgets.

00:18:38.730 --> 00:18:39.120
Yeah.

00:18:39.120 --> 00:18:44.305
That's kind of what you're
looking for to build.

00:18:44.305 --> 00:18:46.680
IAN NI-LEWIS: So congratulations
to Pattrn and

00:18:46.680 --> 00:18:48.570
Tasks for making it
into Pure Android.

