00:20:43.060 --> 00:20:44.800
And another thing that you
should also consider is

00:20:44.800 --> 00:20:46.050
including a promotional video.

00:20:46.050 --> 00:20:48.840
And you can see that there is
a link for one here online.

00:20:48.840 --> 00:20:51.200
Basically you want to do
everything you can to help the

00:20:51.200 --> 00:20:52.880
Google Play team merchandise
your app.

00:20:52.880 --> 00:20:53.690
IAN NI-LEWIS: Absolutely.

00:20:53.690 --> 00:20:55.740
The promo video a lot of people
forget, but it's an

00:20:55.740 --> 00:20:56.940
absolute no-brainer.

00:20:56.940 --> 00:21:00.970
It's absolutely the most
effective way that we've found

00:21:00.970 --> 00:21:03.242
to sell people on your app.

00:21:03.242 --> 00:21:05.530
RETO MEIER: Once you've moved
beyond that, what we really

00:21:05.530 --> 00:21:08.230
want you to look at is the
app quality guidelines.

00:21:08.230 --> 00:21:09.985
Now this is something that you
can find on developer.android.

00:21:09.985 --> 00:21:13.610
com on the Distribute
tab under Google

00:21:13.610 --> 00:21:15.220
Play Quality Core.

00:21:15.220 --> 00:21:17.380
And these are really sort of
the fundamental things.

00:21:17.380 --> 00:21:20.350
So again, when we have people
internally looking at what

00:21:20.350 --> 00:21:22.640
apps can we feature, what things
can we put into pure

00:21:22.640 --> 00:21:25.480
Android, this is basically a
checklist of things which

00:21:25.480 --> 00:21:28.710
we're going to look at as sort
of your bare minimum entry

00:21:28.710 --> 00:21:30.350
requirements for what
we consider that to

00:21:30.350 --> 00:21:31.640
be a quality app.

00:21:31.640 --> 00:21:33.220
IAN NI-LEWIS: Now a lot of
people don't know the story

00:21:33.220 --> 00:21:36.920
behind these, but Reto and I
actually spent months working

00:21:36.920 --> 00:21:43.820
on these pages on convincing
the team to post those

00:21:43.820 --> 00:21:44.610
guidelines.

00:21:44.610 --> 00:21:48.400
Because originally, we just
had a set of internal QA

00:21:48.400 --> 00:21:51.670
guidelines that we would run
any candidate for featuring

00:21:51.670 --> 00:21:54.460
past, and if they failed those
guidelines they'd have to

00:21:54.460 --> 00:21:56.130
either fix it or not
get featured.

00:21:56.130 --> 00:22:00.590
And it took a long time to get
everyone involved to agree to

00:22:00.590 --> 00:22:02.600
post these guidelines online,
but they finally

00:22:02.600 --> 00:22:03.450
are there for you.

00:22:03.450 --> 00:22:07.380
They really are the guidelines
that our QA team uses to

00:22:07.380 --> 00:22:09.740
figure out whether an app
is featureable or not.

00:22:09.740 --> 00:22:12.450
So if you're not meeting these
guidelines, you are not

00:22:12.450 --> 00:22:13.940
meeting the lowest bar.

00:22:13.940 --> 00:22:14.400
RETO MEIER: Exactly.

00:22:14.400 --> 00:22:15.970
So this is something you should
spend a lot of time

00:22:15.970 --> 00:22:17.630
looking over and basically
as part of

00:22:17.630 --> 00:22:19.920
own release QA checklist.

00:22:19.920 --> 00:22:22.390
This is what we recommend you
do, is go through this, make

00:22:22.390 --> 00:22:23.950
sure that you're meeting all
of these requirements.

00:22:23.950 --> 00:22:26.990
And then you'll know that you
have an app that is quality,

00:22:26.990 --> 00:22:29.140
it meets those quality
guidelines.

00:22:29.140 --> 00:22:30.530
IAN NI-LEWIS: Of course,
just having an

00:22:30.530 --> 00:22:31.780
app isn't good enough.

00:22:31.780 --> 00:22:34.910
We also want that app to look
great on different devices.

00:22:34.910 --> 00:22:37.260
And this year, we are
all about tablets.

00:22:37.260 --> 00:22:39.050
So it's got to look
great on tablets.

00:22:39.050 --> 00:22:39.500
RETO MEIER: Exactly.

00:22:39.500 --> 00:22:43.480
And you can find the tablet app
quality checklist also on

00:22:43.480 --> 00:22:44.730
Google Play.

00:22:44.730 --> 00:22:46.420
It's quality/tablet.

00:22:46.420 --> 00:22:49.450
And so you'll find here a bunch
of best practices which

00:22:49.450 --> 00:22:52.320
we look at to say, well, is this
a tablet app, is this not

00:22:52.320 --> 00:22:53.200
a tablet app.

00:22:53.200 --> 00:22:55.190
This is basically what we're
going to look at and what we

00:22:55.190 --> 00:22:58.220
recommend you look at to say,
well, this meets that bar.

00:22:58.220 --> 00:23:00.440
This is something which we think
tablet users are going

00:23:00.440 --> 00:23:04.350
to be able to use and enjoy
on their devices.

